y at this time. Rumors are that is drops off a golem in Chardok, another is that it drops off a dragon in Skyshrine. <p>Chants Evensong
57 Bard Brell Server
Clan Spiritslammer/

Haielor Evensong
Dark Elf Cleric 25
Brell Server
Clan Spiritslammer/

Chants Spiritslammer
Wood Elf Warrior 23
Terris-Thule Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulanaesoulsease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulanae Soulsease</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 4:32:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.wwa.com/~danas/Kulanae4.jpg height=158 width=119></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Yeah that Golem story just doesn't add up to me....I mean why would a golum drop a dragon scale?  I'd be more inclined to think dragon in Skyshrine or Western Wastes. <p><font size=2 face="Tempus Sans ITC, Verdana, Helvetica">
Kulanae Soulsease</font><br>
<font size=2 face="Helvetica">
Bardess of 55 seasons<br>
<a href=http://www.watchers-brell.com/>Watchers Guild</a><br>
<a href=http://www.brellserilis.net/index.shtml>Brell Serilis</a><br>
<br>
<i>Joy is in the ears that hear!</i>
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatterdmalion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatter DMalion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 4:36:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Well, the epics were created with Kunark, basically.  If they stick a part out there in SoV, I think it's a bone-headed idea.  A person should be able to complete their epic using the original expansion only, imho.<br>
<br>
Yes, I know they can TECHNICALLY, but the redistribution should stay in Kunark like the other stuff.<br>
<br>
Tatter D'Malion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>  Posts: 1902<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/6/01 4:02:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soj/itsme.jpg height=153 width=142></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Either of those make 0 sense, if they do anything besides add it to a ragefire like mob that spawns when Vox dies it will be a huge mistake. <p>nillon<br>
60 warlord<br>
<a href ="http://sr.amiga.tm">Silent Redemption</a><br>
Champion of Brell <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualvimar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alvimar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/6/01 4:26:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Well I agree it makes sense Nillon, just not sure if VI has been lately... /shrug<br>
<br>
We'll see when it happens for sure but not holding my breath just yet (only my level a little more than I would normally.. :^\ ) <p><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size="2" font color=#8A2BE2>Bristlebane's best to you all,<br>
Alvimar Beene <<a href=http://www.eqharpers.com>Harpers</a>> (GM)<br>
52nd season Songweaver<br>
Brell Serilis<br><br>
Daealan <<a href=http://www.eqharpers.com>Harpers</a>><br>
21st season Enchanter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lord Chancellor of Brell</span><br>  Posts: 622<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/6/01 8:00:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> I was and still am very dubious about this rumor.  And I think that Tatter makes a pretty good point about keeping the components in Antonica and Kunark.  The scale droping from a golem in Chardok has got to be a fabrication.  This whole rumor sounds like baloney.<br>
<br>
Nillon, that would be a decent idea, having a ragefire-like mob spawn in Vox's lair.<br>
<br>
As it stands now, the bard epic is on the medium to medium-high difficult end of the epic weapon quests.  As anotehr bard on a another server said, this is where it should be. <p>Chants Evensong
57 Bard Brell Server
Clan Spiritslammer/

Haielor Evensong
Dark Elf Cleric 25
Brell Server
Clan Spiritslammer/

Chants Spiritslammer
Wood Elf Warrior 23
Terris-Thule Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualvimar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alvimar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/6/01 3:45:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Just wish there wasn't effectively a level cap on starting it... 53+ need not applie till Gorenaire is being taken regularly.. What is the status on her anyway?  Haven't heard if she's dropping the scales or how well she's being taken down these days... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lord Chancellor of Brell</span><br>  Posts: 624<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/6/01 5:46:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Yes Alvimar.  It is odd to have such a &quot;level cap.&quot;  A bard can effectively get all the components before level 52, except for perhaps Trak guts.  If you were over 52 when the quest was introduced, you may not be able to get a scale until you were able to kill Gorenaire, or could make a deal for a white scale.  That could be several levels.<br>
<br>
But the palidans have the same problem.  One of thier books for the FA drop off only two dragons, Vox and Gorenaire.  <br>
<br>
Either have white scales drop off a ragefire like mob that spawns in Vox's lair.  Or have ragefire drop white scales.  That would be fair.  But being fair and the coding required may be more than what Verant wants to invest, at this time.  <br>
<br>
The alternative is to keep plugging away and know that the epic weapon is just supposed to be hard.  <br>
<br>
At least we aren't mages or wizards.  If any epic weapons need to be looked at agian, I think it is theirs.<br>
<br>
I predict that the white scale is going to cease being the hardest items to get.  For most of the bard weapons obtained so far, I think that the trak guts used for the quest were surplus guts that were either accumulated by certain people before anyone knew what they were for, or before many bards were ready for them.  Thus, they were not the hardest item to get since they were already gotten, and could be multi-quested.  That supply may be running dry.<br>
<br>
Regardless, I am all for getting components for bards.  Kulanae, Chork, Alvi, Molil, Quemn, Tynin, Sedusar, Tatter and many others are ones that come to my mind when I think of deserving bards on this server.  I would like to do what I can, time permitting, to help them out.   <p>Chants Evensong
57 Bard Brell Server
Clan Spiritslammer/

Haielor Evensong
Dark Elf Cleric 25
Brell Server
Clan Spiritslammer/

Chants Spiritslammer
Wood Elf Warrior 23
Terris-Thule Server</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chants</A> at: 3/6/01 4:49:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usedusar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sedusar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/7/01 1:08:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Thanks Chants very noble of you, the idea of having a mob like ragefire spawn in vox's lair is good, bad thing is that he would still be dropping the white scale and that other casters and maybe even guilds would probably do this quest just to get white dragonscale cloaks.<br>
<br>
The golem story sounds like bull, it wouldnt make sense at all...<br>
<br>
dragon in velious, well that would give the higherlevel bards an added chance of getting a white scale so they could get up to par with the bards below 53, but again Tatter is right it would be kinda dumb to put epic items on a new continent...<br>
<br>
Sed in forever hunt of red and white dragon scales... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utinyntinagyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tinyn Tinagyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/19/01 4:59:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Would need to see Vox dieing once in a while for a Vox-Ragefire to be of any use. Much more in favor of just seeing the melee slow removed from Gore then anything else.<br>
<br>
The golem was real on test for a few days, basicly just to get an SSS or two on test since they can't kill Gore. Its been taken out. <p><font size="-1">Tinyn Tinagyn - Yellow and Green Bard of the 52nd Song, on Brell Serilis<br>
Never heard a mole sing before, have you, Trimp?</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatterdmalion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatter DMalion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/19/01 10:20:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: White scale a bards</span><hr size=1> Ok, giving it some more thought, but just not happy with the current situation.  /sigh<br>
<br>
The Scalecollector will only drop red scales.  That's been the drop so far and I don't think it will change.  I believe there must be another mob which drops the white scale, yet to be found.  Currently, whites only come from Vox and Gore, while red comes from Naggy, Ragefire, Tal, and Scalecollector.  Bit of an imbalance I'd say.<br>
<br>
Undead bard...for some reason, I think he is similar to the new trigger for Feyd on the druid epic quest.  Give him something and it respawns Trak, hopefully, a slightly lesser version.  The respawned Trak then drops undead guts ONLY.  The respawned Feyd only drops the globe of water; so that is why I think guts only.  I don't buy having to give him ANY parts of our quest.  That would be too big a change to the quest.  The lute must be another and not the one from Hate either.  It's too uber for a quest item, well, imho.<br>
<br>
The only thing I see wrong so far, except for our lack of knowledge, is the lack of guts from some Trak raids.  It went from every kill to none.  However, it's been my understanding that guts weren't that common to begin with and the current lack of drops is just it's further continuation.  I'm not worried about it yet.<br>
<br>
With all that said, I plan to make a decision during the next 2 weeks.  I've been leveling sense I gave up on Vox.  But sinse Gore seems to be too much trouble to kill for various reasons, I'm back to considering sacrificing myself back to 52 and raiding Vox again to get the scale.  I have no way to make money to buy a cloak.  Gore is not dieing. So until another source of white scales shows up, Vox seems to be the only viable solution at this time.  Lately, I've gotten little enjoyment from raiding.  This dumb sword is the ONLY that keeps me going for some reason and it's starting to sadden me.  Also, bards are no longer special.  Shoot, the other day I got griped at for playing resists songs due to the stupid rollover effect.  I came close to just going solo so I wouldn't screw the other raiders.<br>
<br>
Nillon is partly right, if you have good resist gear, bards are useless for the most part.<br>
<br>
Tatter D'Malion <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=310.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=431.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.threadControl?topicID=417.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=417.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=417.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (Admin only)<option value="brellserilisfrm64">Archived Threads<option value="brellserilismeleetalk">Tome: Races and Classes <option value="brellserilisroleplaying">Tome: History of Norrath<option value="brellserilisfrm49">Tome: Visions of Norrath<option value="brellserilisfrm